03919nam a22005775i 9780292759671DE-B159720211027022714.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211027t20211966txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927596717 a10.7560/7361222doi  a(DE-B1597)586513  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 7aBIO0090002bisacsh1 aDawson, Jerry F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFriedrich Schleiermacher :bThe Evolution of a Nationalist /cJerry F. Dawson. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©1966  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tCONTENTS -- t1. An Introduction to a Philosophy -- t2. Schleiermacher, Rationalism, and Romanticism -- t3. From Satisfaction to the Depths of Despair -- t4. From Prussian Patriotism to German Nationalism -- t5. The War of Liberation -- t6. Schleiermacher during the Period of Reaction -- t7. The Doctrine of the State -- t8. Evaluation of a Nationalist -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aNationalism was a driving, moving spirit in the nineteenth-century Germany of Friedrich Schleiermacher. Jerry F. Dawson, through his thoughtful and well-wrought study of Friedrich Schleiermacher, provides an insight into contemporary nationalistic movements and the people who have a part in them. Schleiermacher, a prominent theologian and educator, was also a leading contributor to the tide of nationalism which swept Germany during the Napoleonic era. Dawson does not present Schleiermacher as an archetype for nationalists, but rather as an example of one man who was willing to sacrifice everything for the good of the nation. Examining the influence of Pietism, rationalism, and romanticism on Schleiermacher, the author explains the origins of his subject's nationalistic activities and traces the evolution of his patriotic point of view. Dawson depicts the development of Schleiermacher's patriotism from Prussian particularism to German nationalism—an allegiance to an idealized Germany unified in religion, language, folkways. He describes the diverse approaches utilized by Schleiermacher to achieve a patriotic awakening among his countrymen: "…he preached nationalistic sermons; he delivered scholarly lectures; he repeatedly risked his life on dangerous missions which would help free Germany from France; he used his journalistic talents to try to stimulate the national consciousness of the German people; and he even served in the government of Prussia in an attempt to reconstruct the educational system so that nationalism might be advanced."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/73612240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292759671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292759671/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK